# Delivery checklist

Use this checklist at a meaningful handoff, review, release, or interview presentation. Mark an item unknown
or not applicable with a reason; unchecked does not mean implicitly accepted.

## Scope and behavior

- [ ] Canonical requirements and acceptance criteria are linked and their status is reported.
- [ ] Consequential decisions, superseded choices, and deviations are current.
- [ ] User-visible behavior, limitations, and unsupported cases are explicit.

## Evidence and risk

- [ ] Material claims link to reproducible evidence with scope and limitations.
- [ ] Applicable module registers are reconciled with their canonical systems.
- [ ] Failed checks, unknowns, residual risks, and follow-up owners are reported.
- [ ] No secret, sensitive payload, prompt, response, personal data, or private endpoint is committed.

## Delivery and recovery

- [ ] Relevant tests and `--check` pass, or failures are explained.
- [ ] Costs and resource consumption are measured, estimated, or explicitly unknown.
- [ ] Operating limits, rollback, recovery, and ownership are documented when applicable.
- [ ] The worklog leaves enough context for another human or agent to continue safely.
